			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p123359">HoH Solo Charming Questions</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Crackity</strong> &raquo; Fri Jul 28, 2006 7:10 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I have read, and committed to memory, the excellent guides on solo charming in HoH South Shrine.  I have been doing it for about one month now, but have a few questions.
<br />
<br />First some background:  Crackity is a 65 Chanter, 57 AAs including Run3, Regen3, SCM3, CA2 and TD3 (plus some others not geared towards charming).  About 4800 HPs and 4500 mana when buffed.  I use SOE or SoW potions when charming and always have Arcane Rune up.  I have Ext Range IV and Spell Haste IV on my gear.
<br />
<br />My main problem is that the mobs seem to be very resistant to root and mezz, and somewhat resistant to CoD.  Infrequently, Pacification causes a 2-mob jail-break, and then we have some fun.  I have found the two entrance mobs (not the Hero Shrine Guardians, just the Valorian Guardians) to be especially bothersome.  I get the majority of my paci resists there, and find that they are the most difficult to root or mezz.  It nothing I can't handle, but I end up burning through my mana to control.
<br />
<br />I have tried both the haste and kill a bunch, as well as even-beatdown, nuke two strategy.  I usually plan on killing many, but if the mob keeps breaking, I will just burn them both down.
<br />
<br />Typically, I will ignore the entrance mobs, go left or right and pacify one mob that guards the entrance to either big room.  Haste him, then kill the other entrance mob and the two guardians in the big room (slowing all of them).  I then check how much health and time left on my pet and usually send it in on the last mob, usually a Valorian Guard.  I tend to then just nuke the Guard, then dispell and nuke my pet.  Where some people say they kill 10 or 12 mobs with one pet, I just don't see how.  I can get one AA in a bit under an hour this way (not counting popping Lesson of the Devoted on).
<br />
<br />I am just wondering if there might be a better way.  I believe I am following the guide, but hearing some people say that they get an AA every 20 mins sounds promising.  I thought of leveling to 66, but don't know if it would help the resists that much.  
<br />
<br />Also, I plan on finishing CA3 with my next 6, but then am somewhat undecided as to the next AAs to get, but I am leaning towards those that will help me charm in HoH better.
<br />
<br />Any advice would be greatly appreciated.
<br />
<br />Crackity</div>

			

		</div>

		
