			<h3 ><a href="#p123363"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Daislet</strong> &raquo; Fri Jul 28, 2006 8:11 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Valorian Guards/Sentry's are lvl 63/64, another lvl for you still puts you within 5 lvls of the mobs for the xp sweet spot and would benefit you with less charm breaks.
<br />Charmed/hasted pet wont last more than 5-6 mobs without rune tanking.
<br />You say the mobs are quite resistant to mez/root....these two spells shouldn't be needed (and would be a mana drain)...you have both Ext Range 4 and Spell Haste 4 items - just get max distance from the mobs on charm breaks, even if it requires running down the hallway a bit and recast CoD, generally you'll still have agro from the mob your pet WAS fighting but you can kite in a tight circle around your pet again till he regains agro.
<br />Make sure your CHA is max'd for less charm breaks.
<br />IMO i can't remember the exact time for an AA but 30-40mins is more likely correct.
<br />
<br />Daislet.</div>

			

		</div>

		
