			<h3 ><a href="#p123416"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Crackity</strong> &raquo; Mon Jul 31, 2006 3:55 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Thanks for the advice.  A few things ...
<br />
<br />Unmei --  I am at the South Hero Shrine, and I am only charming and killing the human guards.  I never even tried the animate armor ... until last night.  A 67 ranger was kiting in the north basement and asked if I wanted to come (we were the only two in the zone).  I had never killed there, so thought I would give it a go.  With his snare, the whole process was trivial -- we ran out of mobs in fact.  He decided to try an animate armor from the entry room.  Woah Nelly.  Unrootable, unsnareable, unmezzable, uncharmable.  We basically took turns running around with aggro while the other took shots at it.  Took about 10 mins.  Last time we tried that.
<br />
<br />Daislet -- I DO need root and mezz because of the resists I am getting.  I always run to get distance and then try to re-COD -- the problem is with the fact that it is getting resisted (or the spell is interupted).  I then take a few hits running past it to get distance, then root or mezz to reestablish CoD.  My charisma is maxed at 280 when I charm.
<br />
<br />Omad -- Really?  Does hitting 66 really kill XP?  That's too bad.  I thought hitting 66 might help with resists while keeping me within 5 lvls of the mobs.  If it is true (and I do believe you), that would put a real crimp in my plan to get to about 200 AAs here (averaging about 2 or 3 a night). 
<br />
<br />Also, just to add fuel to a long-discussed fire.  I notice only a *slight* difference in charm breaks now that I have TD3.  I expected more.
<br />
<br />I just finished CA3, and am thinking about doing ER3 and then LR5 for my next two.  Does that sound about right ?
<br />
<br />Thanks again.
<br />Crackity</div>

			

