	<div id="p123420" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p123420"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Cerpicio</strong> &raquo; Mon Jul 31, 2006 5:12 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I did a lot of soloing in HoH.  At 66 it isn't bad, but noticibly drops off at 67.  That's about the time I moved to Noble's Casueway.
<br />
<br />I'd suggest working on the AAs that increase your CHA cap.  I think that will make a big differenece with you.  I never had problems with root/mez/charm, except the occassional ones you always get.  I just ran till I had room (make sure you have that extended range and spell haste going) and re-charmed my old pet.  Your target should indeed be rooted (the mob your pet attacks).  
<br />
<br />Make sure you give yourself time to come to a complete stop to avoid the interrupts.  Run a little further than you think you need, and try casting.  You should get the &quot;target out of range&quot; message.  Just keep trying to cast until he is in range.  If that happens and you still can't get the spell off before the ex-pet gets to you...well, something is wrong.
<br />
<br />I had it down so well I could clear both sides, plus the four at the entrance, and get back to the first spot about the time mobs were respawning.
<br />
<br />
<br />-- C.
<br />PS: A little more info:
<br />1. Paci one of the pair. 
<br />2. Target the second, turn and face the way you're going to run, and tash the second mob. (Oh, you should already be about max distance from him)
<br />3. Start running.  Just how far is hard to explain, but it sounds like you have the general idea.  Come to a COMPLETE stop and start casting CoD.
<br />4. Mob should be charmed.  Return to first mob.
<br />
<br />If you can get reliable roots, root the target mob, then tash and slow before sending in your pet.  Otherwise send in pet and let him get agro before you cast on the target.  Tash, root, slow.  Have your clicky-damage-ring handy and wait till the target is low on HP or you'll break root too soon.
<br />
<br />Always be ready to run in case charm breaks early, and always be as far from the fight as possible.</div>

			

		</div>

		
