			<h3 ><a href="#p123447"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Saellis</strong> &raquo; Tue Aug 01, 2006 2:05 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Pulling with tash (or bcb clickie then tash) and using greater fetter for root should reduce resists to all but an afterthought. I'm just mentioning for clarification of what spells you're using.
<br />
<br />People that get an AA in under a half hour without lesson of gimmexp generally don't do that self buffed with minimal AA's and lackluster gear. That is to say, they can blur-nuke every mob without dying or stopping for maximum xp. 
<br />
<br />My hasted pet generally lasted through 3~5 slowed mobs without any other assistance. Pets that last longer do so because the enchanter is putting additional effort, like slowing <span style="font-style: italic">and</span> heavily nuking. (not counting blurring your pet aftera  charm break so it regens to full hp)
<br />
<br />I averaged 40 minutes per AA without lesson of PLmeplz by doing 5 points of damage per mob, and ignoring memblur... unless I wanted to keep the same pet. 
<br />
<br />Blurring for full xp is more xp <span style="font-style: italic">per mob</span>, but only more per hour if you can afford the additional mana cost. If you have downtime because of it, don't do it. 
<br />
<br />&lt;3 goblin gazughi ring and total domination.</div>

