			<h3 ><a href="#p123471"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Yakk</strong> &raquo; Tue Aug 01, 2006 8:01 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I only lull-split mobs when I have a charmed pet ready to engage.
<br />
<br />If your charmed pet is dead, simply tash one mob at max range, run away, then cast charm on the tashed mob &amp; /pet attack the other mob.
<br />
<br />If you have a charmed pet ready, lull one, tash the other, and use your pet as a speedbump.  -aggro foci for tash (PoInn lever, etc) may be useful so your pet can pull aggro off of you.  Root is also good for this purpose.
<br />
<br />If lull resists, you will have your pet.  He can engage, you assist your pet, tash his target, then mez his target.  Tash the other mob, mez it.  Now things are under control.
<br />
<br />The mob AI used to let you run by them quite often if you had enough runspeed, and hugged the walls.</div>

			

		</div>

		
