	<div id="p123492" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p123492"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Crackity</strong> &raquo; Wed Aug 02, 2006 1:57 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Again, thank you all for your valuable advice.  I have tried almost every piece of advice given (I especially like the comment to use your pet as a &quot;speed bump&quot;), and have found each to be helpful.
<br />
<br />I have settled into a fairly standard procedure -- I start on either side, paci one, tash, run and charm pet -- haste him and set him on the pacified mob, which I slow and tag with the BCB, I then keep it rooted and sit to regen.  Without any charm break, I can then use the hasted pet to kill the remaining three mobs on the side, although it's about 50/50% whether the pet will last through the last guard, usually a Valorian Guard, rather than a Guardian.  If it gets close enough, I will break charm and nuke the final two.  In any event, if the pet kills the guard, I then nuke the pet down.  I then go to the other side and do the same.
<br />
<br />Because I have found the two Guardians near the entrance to be quite resistant, I then handle them as a pair.  Paci, tash, charm, no haste.  Let them fight evenly, break charm and nuke the pair.  A &quot;typical&quot; run will therefore be (8 x 3.5 = 28%) + (4 x 5.5% = 22%) = 50%, and takes about 25 minutes.  It will often be a bit slower, although sometimes I will nuke down more mobs, at the cost of mana, of course.  After one &quot;round&quot; I typically have to med for about 10 mins.  It, therefore works out to almost exactly one hour per AA.  Each night I am also using Lesson of the Devoted, so one round will usually ping me.
<br />
<br />What I have realized is that I need to get some more mana regen -- right now I just have it at 2 (Coldain Shawl at lvl 7 and Earring of the Solstice).  One easy upgrade is to finish the shawl (just need to talk my guild into the assisting on the walk - have everything done).  I am also looking into the DoN augs on the DoN armor, but have been unable to find ANY Master or Grandmaster Starglow armor on Povar.  The plat isn't much of a concern, but there simply isn't any to buy.  Once I get more FT, I think I may switch over to breaking charm and nuking them down in pairs -- the idea of 12 x 5.5% = 66% per round is tempting.
<br />
<br />I also think I will move on to lvl 66 -- from reading other posts, I don't think there will be much, if any, XP loss.  The Guards and Guardians are lvl 62; the Sentries are 63.  At 66, I will still be well withing the 5 lvl limit, and the 1st lvl 66 spell -- Ethereal Rune (1950hps) will probably eliminate any deaths in HoH -- I admit it, about once a week, I get sloppy -- don't really die anymore, just gate).
<br />
<br />Again, thanks for all of the expert advice,
<br />Crackity</div>

			

		</div>

		
