		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p123496"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Yakk</strong> &raquo; Wed Aug 02, 2006 3:01 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">The &quot;within 5 level Xp bonus&quot; is not a binary switch.  Within 4 levels gives more Xp than within 4 levels, etc.
<br />
<br />Three is a sharp drop going from 5 under to 6 under, however.
<br />
<br />...
<br />
<br />If you have two mobs, and you have no pet, seriously try:
<br />tash one, run, charm that one, /pet attack other
<br />
<br />It is more reliable than lull/tash/charm.
<br />
<br />For the two high-MR mobs, have a relatively high HP pet, lull one, tash the other, pet engage, BCB.  Repeat for other mob.  On a lull aggro, pet engage, assist pet, tash, mez.
<br />
<br />All Damage Is Good Damage.  Letting your pet get beat up more isn't a bad thing.
<br />
<br />I tend to say &quot;screw nuking the pet down&quot;.  Just break charm, root, charm another NPC, and kill the ex-pet.  This may or may not be XP optimal, but I definately found it more fun.  :)</div>

			

		</div>

		
